37
00:03:07.110 --> 00:03:10.030
That's a funny one.
Isn't that funnier?

38
00:03:10.150 --> 00:03:11.320
It's hysterical. Manny.

39
00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:14.280
As long as we're laughing.
we won't cry over the box office.

40
00:03:14.400 --> 00:03:15.950
Talk about depressing.

41
00:03:16.070 --> 00:03:19.530
Twenty girls in feather boas
prancing around like circus ponies.

42
00:03:19.660 --> 00:03:21.160
That's depressing.

43
00:03:21.290 --> 00:03:23.544
I love a good chorus line.

44
00:03:25.374 --> 00:03:28.174
- What's this?
- It's a play.

45
00:03:28.294 --> 00:03:29.714
Who wrote it. Annie?

46
00:03:29.834 --> 00:03:31.594
Some guy. Driscoll.

47
00:03:32.094 --> 00:03:33.304
Driscoll.

48
00:03:33.424 --> 00:03:35.214
From the Federal Theatre.

49
00:03:35.344 --> 00:03:38.674
Don't knock it. honey. At
least they got an audience.

50
00:03:39.384 --> 00:03:42.264
It'll pick up. Isn't
that right. Manny?

51
00:03:46.014 --> 00:03:47.518
It always does.

52
00:03:48.438 --> 00:03:49.528
See you tomorrow.

53
00:03:49.648 --> 00:03:53.698
The trick is to start to build
right from the back of your throat.

54
00:03:55.408 --> 00:03:57.368
Works well out
through the nose. too.

55
00:03:57.488 --> 00:03:59.238
Have you eaten today?

56
00:04:00.618 --> 00:04:02.868
I'm not hungry.
Don't worry about me.

57
00:04:03.038 --> 00:04:04.158
Hey.

58
00:04:05.458 --> 00:04:07.208
You're all I've got.

59
00:04:08.708 --> 00:04:10.878
Come on. take me to dinner.

60
00:04:11.752 --> 00:04:12.882
Okay.

61
00:04:13.302 --> 00:04:16.092
You think the kitchen will
still be open on Third?

62
00:04:16.382 --> 00:04:18.722
Soup and biscuits. Perfect.

63
00:04:25.602 --> 00:04:27.722
Harry. what's going on?

64
00:04:29.022 --> 00:04:32.232
- Hey. open up! We work here.
- Not anymore. lady.

65
00:04:32.352 --> 00:04:35.906
It's all right for you. We haven't
had a paycheck in two weeks.

66
00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:37.616
How we gonna eat?

67
00:04:37.866 --> 00:04:40.826
- They're not getting away with this!
- They just did.

68
00:04:40.946 --> 00:04:43.326
Ann. it's no use.

69
00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:46.326
The show. it's over. It's done.

70
00:04:47.166 --> 00:04:48.416
I'm done.

71
00:04:50.876 --> 00:04:52.586
I'm leaving. Annie.

72
00:04:54.336 --> 00:04:56.336
I'm going back to Chicago.

73
00:04:57.296 --> 00:04:58.800
I'm sorry.

74
00:04:59.970 --> 00:05:01.550
I'm sorry. Annie.

75
00:05:03.550 --> 00:05:06.930
Ever since you were small.
people been letting you down.

76
00:05:08.680 --> 00:05:10.940
You gotta think of yourself now.

77
00:05:11.230 --> 00:05:13.770
You should try out for that part.

78
00:05:16.570 --> 00:05:18.860
Oh. I know what you're thinking.

79
00:05:19.570 --> 00:05:22.824
Every time you reach out for
something you care about...

80
00:05:22.954 --> 00:05:25.614
fate comes along
and snatches it away.

81
00:05:26.324 --> 00:05:28.284
But not this time. Annie.

82
00:05:28.954 --> 00:05:30.414
Not this time.

83
00:05:35.334 --> 00:05:37.674
- Oh. hello. Mr Weston.
- Oh. jeez.

84
00:05:37.924 --> 00:05:40.794
Look. miss. I told you
already. call my office.

85
00:05:40.924 --> 00:05:42.794
Leave your résumé with my secretary.

86
00:05:42.924 --> 00:05:45.968
Now. why would I want to do that
when we can talk about it in person?

87
00:05:46.098 --> 00:05:47.638
Because that's what
a smart girl would do.

88
00:05:47.768 --> 00:05:50.188
But I already sent you my
résumé. You returned it unopened.

89
00:05:50.308 --> 00:05:53.308
What can I say? Jack Driscoll's very
particular about who he works with.

90
00:05:53.438 --> 00:05:55.018
Please. just an audition.
That's all I'm asking.

91
00:05:55.148 --> 00:05:56.318
Jesus. you don't give up. do you?

92
00:05:56.438 --> 00:05:57.938
Mr Weston. I know
this role backwards.

93
00:05:58.068 --> 00:06:00.988
Well. that's too bad. 'cause we
just gave the part to someone else.

94
00:06:01.108 --> 00:06:03.448
I'm sorry. kid. The play is cast.

95
00:06:07.568 --> 00:06:09.198
I know times are tough.

96
00:06:09.742 --> 00:06:11.292
You want my advice?

97
00:06:11.582 --> 00:06:14.662
Use what you got.
You're not bad-looking.

98
00:06:14.792 --> 00:06:17.372
A girl like you
doesn't have to starve.

99
00:06:19.632 --> 00:06:22.092
There's a new place. It just opened.

100
00:06:26.722 --> 00:06:30.302
Now listen. princess. this gig
ain't the Palace. you understand?

101
00:06:30.432 --> 00:06:33.356
Ask for Kenny K.
Tell him I sent you.

102
00:06:34.606 --> 00:06:37.066
Just play the date.
take the money...

103
00:06:38.066 --> 00:06:40.026
forget you was ever there.

104
00:07:10.220 --> 00:07:12.100
How much more is there?

105
00:07:12.680 --> 00:07:14.350
Another five reels.

106
00:07:14.760 --> 00:07:16.060
Lights up.

107
00:07:24.024 --> 00:07:25.364
This is it?

108
00:07:26.074 --> 00:07:28.234
This is what we get
for our $40.000. Denham?

109
00:07:28.364 --> 00:07:29.944
Another one of your safari pictures?

110
00:07:30.074 --> 00:07:33.114
You promised us romantic scenes with
Bruce Baxter and Maureen McKenzie!

111
00:07:33.244 --> 00:07:34.864
Come on. fellows. you know the deal.

112
00:07:34.994 --> 00:07:36.534
We agreed to push
Maureen's start date...

113
00:07:36.664 --> 00:07:38.204
so she could get her teeth fixed.

114
00:07:38.324 --> 00:07:41.084
It's not the principle of
the thing. it's the money.

115
00:07:41.204 --> 00:07:43.704
Carl. you've been in
production for over two months.

116
00:07:43.834 --> 00:07:46.508
Trust me. Bruce and Maureen
are gonna steam up the screen...

117
00:07:46.588 --> 00:07:48.428
once we get them on the ship.

118
00:07:49.258 --> 00:07:50.548
What ship?

119
00:07:50.848 --> 00:07:53.428
The one that we hired
to get to the location.

120
00:07:53.558 --> 00:07:57.308
What location? Carl! You're supposed
to be shooting on the back lot.

121
00:07:57.428 --> 00:07:58.888
Yes. I understand that.

122
00:07:59.018 --> 00:08:01.348
But. fellows. we're not
making that film anymore...

123
00:08:01.478 --> 00:08:02.688
and I'll tell you why.

124
00:08:02.808 --> 00:08:05.568
The story has changed. The
script has been rewritten.

125
00:08:05.688 --> 00:08:07.778
Life intervened.

126
00:08:08.782 --> 00:08:11.242
I've come into possession of a map.

127
00:08:12.572 --> 00:08:15.702
The sole surviving record
of an uncharted island.

128
00:08:15.872 --> 00:08:18.912
A place that was thought
to exist only in myth.

129
00:08:19.242 --> 00:08:20.242
Until now.

130
00:08:20.372 --> 00:08:22.332
Whoa. Carl. slow down.

131
00:08:22.452 --> 00:08:23.752
Is he asking for more money?

132
00:08:23.872 --> 00:08:26.422
He's asking us to fund
a wild-goose chase.

133
00:08:26.542 --> 00:08:30.922
I'm talking about a primitive
world never before seen by man.

134
00:08:32.136 --> 00:08:35.096
The ruins of an entire civilisation.

135
00:08:36.426 --> 00:08:39.266
The most spectacular
thing you've ever seen.

136
00:08:40.346 --> 00:08:42.806
That's where I'll shoot my picture.

137
00:08:45.356 --> 00:08:47.186
Will there be boobies?

138
00:08:48.486 --> 00:08:49.646
Boobies?

139
00:08:50.146 --> 00:08:52.816
Jigglies. Jiblonkas. Bazooms.

140
00:08:53.066 --> 00:08:55.740
In my experience. people
only go to these films...

141
00:08:55.820 --> 00:08:59.120
to observe the undraped
form of the native girls.

142
00:08:59.330 --> 00:09:00.740
What are you. an idiot?

143
00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:04.040
You think they asked De Mille if he
would waste his time on nudie shots?

144
00:09:04.160 --> 00:09:07.750
No! They respected the
filmmaker. They showed some class.

145
00:09:07.880 --> 00:09:11.250
Not that you'd know what
that means. you cheap lowlife!

146
00:09:15.470 --> 00:09:18.050
Would you step out
for a moment. Carl?

147
00:09:31.814 --> 00:09:33.524
Give me that. quick.

148
00:09:35.234 --> 00:09:37.234
You won't like it.
It's non-alcoholic.

149
00:09:37.364 --> 00:09:41.404
Preston. you have a lot to learn
about the motion picture business.

150
00:09:44.368 --> 00:09:46.958
Don't write him off.
fellows. He's hotheaded. sure...

151
00:09:47.078 --> 00:09:49.958
but Carl Denham's made
some interesting pictures.

152
00:09:50.088 --> 00:09:52.338
He's had a lot of near-success.

153
00:09:52.918 --> 00:09:54.838
He's a preening self-promoter.

154
00:09:54.968 --> 00:09:58.218
An ambitious no-talent. The guy's
got "loser" written all over him.

155
00:09:58.338 --> 00:10:00.798
I understand your disappointment-
He can't direct.

156
00:10:00.928 --> 00:10:03.508
- He doesn't have the smarts.
He's washed up.

157
00:10:03.638 --> 00:10:05.308
It's all over town.

158
00:10:05.718 --> 00:10:08.392
This jumped-up little
turd's gonna bankrupt us.

159
00:10:08.482 --> 00:10:10.272
The animal footage has value.

160
00:10:10.392 --> 00:10:12.772
Sure. Universal are
desperate for stock footage.

161
00:10:12.902 --> 00:10:15.232
Then sell it! Scrap the picture.

162
00:10:18.032 --> 00:10:20.692
We got to retrieve
something from this debacle.

163
00:10:22.612 --> 00:10:24.162
Get him back in.

164
00:10:25.282 --> 00:10:26.822
Mr Denham.

165
00:10:29.872 --> 00:10:32.006
I want the cast and crew
on the ship within the hour.

166
00:10:32.126 --> 00:10:33.206
No. Carl. you can't do this.

167
00:10:33.336 --> 00:10:35.466
Tell them the studio pressured
us into an early departure.

168
00:10:35.586 --> 00:10:37.546
- It's not ethical!
- What are they gonna do. sue me?

169
00:10:37.676 --> 00:10:38.716
They can get in line.

170
00:10:38.836 --> 00:10:40.216
I'm not gonna let them kill my film.

171
00:10:40.346 --> 00:10:43.716
You realise that none of
the camera equipment is on board?

172
00:10:43.846 --> 00:10:46.596
We have no permits. no visas.

173
00:10:46.726 --> 00:10:48.306
That's why I
have you. Preston.

174
00:10:48.436 --> 00:10:50.476
We have no insurance. we
have no foreign currency.

175
00:10:50.596 --> 00:10:52.476
In fact. we have no
currency of any kind.

176
00:10:52.606 --> 00:10:53.646
He's there.

177
00:10:53.766 --> 00:10:55.440
- Get in there.
- Who's gonna pay for the ship?

178
00:10:55.570 --> 00:10:56.610
Get in.

179
00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:03.070
- You get out of there! Come here!
- Step on it! Step on it!

180
00:11:03.200 --> 00:11:06.200
Get out! You're finished. Denham!

181
00:11:09.160 --> 00:11:12.410
Don't worry. Preston. I've
had a lot of practice at this.

182
00:11:13.460 --> 00:11:16.040
I'm real good at
crapping the crappers.

183
00:11:17.460 --> 00:11:21.384
Red Label. 80% proof. to be
packed in a crate marked "lemonade."

184
00:11:21.504 --> 00:11:22.554
You got it.

185
00:11:22.674 --> 00:11:24.964
Tell Maureen she doesn't have
six hours to put on her face.

186
00:11:25.094 --> 00:11:27.344
If she wants to be in this picture.
she's gotta be on that boat.

187
00:11:27.474 --> 00:11:30.014
She doesn't wanna
be in this picture.

188
00:11:31.224 --> 00:11:33.814
- Maureen pulled out.
- She pulled out?

189
00:11:33.934 --> 00:11:35.974
Yesterday. I told you.

190
00:11:36.354 --> 00:11:38.684
You said we were shooting
in Singapore. right?

191
00:11:38.814 --> 00:11:40.734
That's what you told her.

192
00:11:41.234 --> 00:11:43.818
Yeah. but we're not
shooting in Singapore.

193
00:11:43.948 --> 00:11:48.198
God damn it. Preston. all you had to
do was look her in the eye and lie.

194
00:11:48.488 --> 00:11:50.998
I got to get to a phone.
talk to Harlow's people.

195
00:11:51.118 --> 00:11:52.498
She's unavailable.

196
00:11:52.618 --> 00:11:55.368
Myrna Loy?
Clara Bow? Mae West?

197
00:11:55.748 --> 00:11:57.748
You'll never
get her into a size four.

198
00:11:57.878 --> 00:12:01.378
You gotta get a girl that'll
fit into Maureen's costumes.

199
00:12:03.838 --> 00:12:04.968
Fay's a size four.

200
00:12:05.088 --> 00:12:08.552
Yes. she is. but she's
doing a picture with RKO.

201
00:12:10.262 --> 00:12:11.602
Cooper. huh?

202
00:12:13.432 --> 00:12:15.142
I might have known.

203
00:12:15.972 --> 00:12:17.892
You're not listening.
We got to delay the shoot.

204
00:12:18.022 --> 00:12:20.442
Shut production down.
We can't sail tonight.

205
00:12:20.562 --> 00:12:21.942
- Not an option.
- Carl.

206
00:12:22.062 --> 00:12:23.482
I said I'd find a girl.

207
00:12:23.612 --> 00:12:25.822
For God's sake. Preston.
think like a winner!

208
00:12:25.942 --> 00:12:28.732
Call Jack. I need that
goddamn screenplay!

209
00:12:30.616 --> 00:12:32.656
Defeat is always momentary.

210
00:13:06.650 --> 00:13:07.690
What?

211
00:14:01.998 --> 00:14:05.292
Hey! You gonna pay for this?

212
00:14:06.582 --> 00:14:07.882
Excuse me.

213
00:14:10.132 --> 00:14:12.422
Ma'am. I think you dropped this.

214
00:14:22.012 --> 00:14:23.642
Vaudeville. huh?

215
00:14:23.762 --> 00:14:26.772
I worked vaudeville once.
That is a tough audience.

216
00:14:26.892 --> 00:14:28.646
If you don't kill them
fast. they kill you.

217
00:14:28.776 --> 00:14:30.146
Mr Denham...

218
00:14:31.106 --> 00:14:32.196
I want you to know...

219
00:14:32.316 --> 00:14:35.076
that I'm not in the habit of
accepting charity from strangers.

220
00:14:35.196 --> 00:14:36.986
Or. for that matter...

221
00:14:37.656 --> 00:14:39.616
taking things that
don't belong to me.

222
00:14:39.746 --> 00:14:41.616
It was obviously a
terrible misunderstanding.

223
00:14:41.746 --> 00:14:43.616
It's just that I haven't
been paid in a while.

224
00:14:43.746 --> 00:14:47.126
That's awful. Anyway.
Ann... May I call you Ann?

225
00:14:50.246 --> 00:14:53.590
You wouldn't happen to be
a size four. by any chance?

226
00:14:56.180 --> 00:14:58.140
No. no. Oh. God. no.

227
00:14:58.260 --> 00:15:00.760
You've got me all wrong.
Miss Darrow. please.

228
00:15:00.890 --> 00:15:02.930
I'm not that type of person at all.

229
00:15:03.060 --> 00:15:04.680
What type of person are you?

230
00:15:04.810 --> 00:15:07.730
I'm someone you can trust.
Ann. I'm a movie producer.

231
00:15:07.850 --> 00:15:11.860
Believe me. I am on the level. No
funny business. Please sit down.

232
00:15:12.190 --> 00:15:14.480
Please. Please.

233
00:15:18.444 --> 00:15:19.494
Okay.

234
00:15:21.534 --> 00:15:23.034
Ann. I want you to imagine...

235
00:15:23.164 --> 00:15:25.824
a handsome explorer
bound for the Far East.

236
00:15:25.914 --> 00:15:28.164
You're filming in the Far East?

237
00:15:28.414 --> 00:15:29.704
Singapore.

238
00:15:31.794 --> 00:15:34.544
On board ship. he
meets a mysterious girl.

239
00:15:34.874 --> 00:15:38.464
She's beautiful.
she's fragile. haunted.

240
00:15:39.098 --> 00:15:42.218
And she can't escape the feeling
that forces beyond her control...

241
00:15:42.348 --> 00:15:46.178
are compelling her down a road
from which she cannot draw back.

242
00:15:46.558 --> 00:15:50.478
It's as if her whole life has
been a prelude to this moment...

243
00:15:52.358 --> 00:15:56.188
this fateful meeting
that changes everything.

244
00:15:57.318 --> 00:16:00.858
And sure enough. against
her better judgement...

245
00:16:01.148 --> 00:16:02.608
She falls in love.

246
00:16:03.372 --> 00:16:04.372
Yes.

247
00:16:04.572 --> 00:16:06.532
But she doesn't trust it.

248
00:16:06.782 --> 00:16:09.662
She's not even sure if
she believes in love.

249
00:16:12.252 --> 00:16:13.372
Really?

250
00:16:13.582 --> 00:16:15.922
If she loves someone. it's doomed.

251
00:16:16.042 --> 00:16:17.382
Why is that?

252
00:16:17.922 --> 00:16:20.382
Good things never last. Mr Denham.

253
00:16:26.132 --> 00:16:28.476
So you're interested.
Good. That's settled. then.

254
00:16:28.596 --> 00:16:31.056
Now. I don't wanna rush you. but
we are under some time pressure.

255
00:16:31.186 --> 00:16:33.566
- Well. I really-
- Ann. I'm telling you...

256
00:16:33.686 --> 00:16:34.976
you're perfect. Look at you.

257
00:16:35.106 --> 00:16:37.066
You're the saddest
girl I've ever met.

258
00:16:37.186 --> 00:16:41.236
You're gonna make them weep. Ann.
You're gonna break their hearts.

259
00:16:42.616 --> 00:16:44.576
See. that's where
you're wrong. Mr Denham.

260
00:16:44.696 --> 00:16:47.236
I make people laugh.
that's what I do.

261
00:16:47.786 --> 00:16:49.906
Good luck with your picture.

262
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:55.290
Ann? Miss Darrow. please!

263
00:16:55.420 --> 00:16:56.750
I'm offering you money.

264
00:16:56.880 --> 00:17:00.500
Adventure. fame. the thrill of a
lifetime. and a long sea voyage.

265
00:17:00.630 --> 00:17:01.670
You want to read a script?

266
00:17:01.800 --> 00:17:04.800
Jack Driscoll's turning
in a draft as we speak.

267
00:17:06.760 --> 00:17:08.180
Jack Driscoll?

268
00:17:08.300 --> 00:17:09.600
Sure. Why?

269
00:17:09.720 --> 00:17:11.640
Wait. You know him?

270
00:17:12.810 --> 00:17:16.274
No. not personally.
I've seen his plays.

271
00:17:16.434 --> 00:17:18.354
What a writer. huh? And
let me tell you. Ann...

272
00:17:18.484 --> 00:17:21.444
Jack Driscoll does not want just
anyone starring in this picture.

273
00:17:21.564 --> 00:17:22.904
He said to me. "Carl...

274
00:17:23.024 --> 00:17:26.324
"somewhere out there is a
woman born to play this role."

275
00:17:26.444 --> 00:17:28.784
And as soon as I saw you. I knew.

276
00:17:31.154 --> 00:17:32.454
Knew what?

277
00:17:34.494 --> 00:17:36.704
It was always going to be you.

278
00:17:48.848 --> 00:17:51.218
How much do I owe you?
Make it a quarter.

279
00:17:51.348 --> 00:17:52.888
Keep the change.

280
00:17:54.428 --> 00:17:56.728
Is this the moving picture ship?

281
00:17:58.348 --> 00:17:59.728
Not exactly.

282
00:17:59.848 --> 00:18:02.232
It's actually this one over here.

283
00:18:11.822 --> 00:18:15.912
Don't let appearances deceive you.
It's much more spacious on board.

284
00:18:17.202 --> 00:18:18.832
- Is this all of the equipment?
- Yeah.

285
00:18:18.952 --> 00:18:20.002
- This is all of it?
- Yeah.

286
00:18:20.122 --> 00:18:21.662
- We're taking the Bell & Howell?
- Yeah.

287
00:18:21.792 --> 00:18:24.462
- Good. You got all the lenses?
- Sure.

288
00:18:24.582 --> 00:18:26.086
Carl!
- Yes!

289
00:18:26.216 --> 00:18:28.506
Get it on board. fellows. come on.

290
00:18:32.216 --> 00:18:33.306
It's bad. it's bad.

291
00:18:33.426 --> 00:18:35.306
They're on their way.
I've just had word.

292
00:18:35.426 --> 00:18:37.476
- Who?
- Men in uniform.

293
00:18:37.596 --> 00:18:39.646
The studio called the cops.

294
00:18:42.186 --> 00:18:44.146
Englehorn! Cast off!

295
00:18:44.276 --> 00:18:46.146
Hoist up the mainsail.
raise the anchor...

296
00:18:46.276 --> 00:18:48.276
whatever the hell it is
you do. We gotta leave!

297
00:18:48.396 --> 00:18:49.990
I cannot do that.

298
00:18:50.450 --> 00:18:52.320
We are waiting on the manifest.

299
00:18:52.450 --> 00:18:54.870
What? Who? English. please.

300
00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:56.990
Paperwork. Mr Denham.

301
00:18:58.080 --> 00:19:00.750
I'll give you another
$1.000 to leave now.

302
00:19:00.830 --> 00:19:03.210
You haven't given me
the first $1.000 yet.

303
00:19:04.210 --> 00:19:05.460
Can we talk about this later?

304
00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:08.340
Can't you see we're in
the company of a VIP guest?

305
00:19:14.224 --> 00:19:15.474
Ma'am.

306
00:19:16.384 --> 00:19:17.724
Ann Darrow.

307
00:19:18.934 --> 00:19:21.894
So you are ready for
this voyage. Miss Darrow?

308
00:19:22.224 --> 00:19:23.274
Sure.

309
00:19:25.234 --> 00:19:26.394
Nervous?

310
00:19:29.064 --> 00:19:30.944
Nervous? No.

311
00:19:31.444 --> 00:19:34.234
Why? Should I be?

312
00:19:34.734 --> 00:19:37.408
It isn't every woman who
would take such a risk.

313
00:19:40.118 --> 00:19:43.498
Why don't I show Miss
Darrow to her cabin?

314
00:19:44.038 --> 00:19:46.378
Wonderful idea. Thank you. Preston.

315
00:19:46.498 --> 00:19:48.878
Miss Darrow. if you would just...

316
00:19:50.838 --> 00:19:54.258
Hi. My name is Preston.
Carl's assistant.

317
00:19:54.548 --> 00:19:57.388
$2.000. It's a deal.
Will you take a cheque?

318
00:19:58.008 --> 00:19:59.718
Do I have a choice?

319
00:20:00.932 --> 00:20:02.272
Please follow me.

320
00:20:02.392 --> 00:20:04.602
If there's anything that
you... Excuse me. fellows.

321
00:20:04.732 --> 00:20:08.562
If there's anything that you
need. please don't hesitate to ask.

322
00:20:27.126 --> 00:20:29.416
Oh. Jesus! Jack. you scared me.

323
00:20:29.546 --> 00:20:33.926
Listen. If anyone comes to the door.
don't open it. You haven't seen me.

324
00:20:34.086 --> 00:20:36.586
Say I got depressed
and committed suicide.

325
00:20:36.716 --> 00:20:38.846
Say I stuck my head down the toilet.

326
00:20:39.806 --> 00:20:41.846
- You want one?
- No. I can't stay. Carl.

327
00:20:41.966 --> 00:20:44.926
I got a rehearsal for which
I am now three hours late.

328
00:20:45.886 --> 00:20:48.190
- What's this?
- It's the script.

329
00:20:51.310 --> 00:20:52.940
This is a script?

330
00:20:53.570 --> 00:20:55.780
Jack. this is 15 pages.

331
00:20:55.900 --> 00:20:58.490
I know. but they're good. You've
got 15 good pages there. Carl.

332
00:20:58.610 --> 00:21:00.570
I'm supposed to be making
a feature-length picture.

333
00:21:00.700 --> 00:21:03.030
You told me I had more time.
I'm sorry. Look. I gotta go.

334
00:21:03.160 --> 00:21:05.120
No. Jack. you can't do this
to me. I have a beginning...

335
00:21:05.240 --> 00:21:07.830
but I need a middle and an end.
I gotta have something to shoot.

336
00:21:07.950 --> 00:21:11.124
Look. you got my notes.
I got to go. pal. See you.

337
00:21:15.584 --> 00:21:18.094
All right. fine. We
might as well settle up.

338
00:21:19.634 --> 00:21:20.964
You're gonna pay me?

339
00:21:21.094 --> 00:21:22.974
I'm not gonna stiff a friend.

340
00:21:25.184 --> 00:21:27.974
I've never known you to
volunteer cash before.

341
00:21:28.094 --> 00:21:29.854
How's $2.000 sound?

342
00:21:31.564 --> 00:21:32.974
Sounds great.

343
00:21:33.104 --> 00:21:34.774
I thought it might.

344
00:21:34.898 --> 00:21:37.358
- Sounds great.
- Okay.

345
00:21:50.498 --> 00:21:52.038
And voilà.

346
00:21:52.748 --> 00:21:53.918
Thanks.

347
00:21:56.708 --> 00:21:58.802
You've written "two grand."

348
00:22:01.012 --> 00:22:04.632
So I did. Sorry about that.
Let's start from the beginning.

349
00:22:05.012 --> 00:22:07.392
"Two thousand dollars."

350
00:22:15.352 --> 00:22:16.982
It is the 29th. isn't it?

351
00:22:17.102 --> 00:22:19.812
Oh. come on. it's the
25th. It's the 25th.

352
00:22:20.232 --> 00:22:22.446
God. I'm sorry.
It'll just take a sec.

353
00:22:22.576 --> 00:22:24.656
Never mind. Carl. Just
pay me when you get back.

354
00:22:24.786 --> 00:22:26.116
All right.

355
00:22:39.546 --> 00:22:42.586
Your cabin is the last
on the left. Mr Baxter.

356
00:22:42.716 --> 00:22:47.180
And may I just say how excited we
are to have you back with us. sir?

357
00:22:47.300 --> 00:22:49.010
Be a sport and lend a
hand here. would you?

358
00:22:49.140 --> 00:22:51.560
Excuse me. I'm trying
to... I gotta get-

359
00:22:54.230 --> 00:22:55.350
Christ!

360
00:22:56.230 --> 00:22:58.060
Appreciate the help. fellow.

361
00:22:58.190 --> 00:23:00.270
Let me get the door for you.

362
00:23:01.060 --> 00:23:03.520
Welcome to your stateroom. sir.

363
00:23:09.110 --> 00:23:11.164
Dead slow ahead both. Mr Hayes.

364
00:23:11.284 --> 00:23:13.164
Dead slow ahead both. Captain.

365
00:23:21.084 --> 00:23:22.504
Oh. Christ!

366
00:23:31.924 --> 00:23:33.304
God damn it!

367
00:23:41.768 --> 00:23:45.148
I keep telling you. Jack.
there's no money in theatre.

368
00:23:48.198 --> 00:23:49.698
Oh. no! No!

369
00:23:51.158 --> 00:23:53.908
You're much better
off sticking with film.

370
00:23:54.198 --> 00:23:56.578
I don't do it for the money. Carl.

371
00:23:58.042 --> 00:24:00.212
I happen to love the theatre.

372
00:24:00.662 --> 00:24:02.122
No. you don't.

373
00:24:03.462 --> 00:24:05.422
If you really loved it...

374
00:24:05.882 --> 00:24:07.422
you would have jumped.

375
00:24:27.566 --> 00:24:30.696
This room very comfortable.
Plenty dim light. fresh straw.

376
00:24:30.816 --> 00:24:32.776
Jesus. What do you keep down here?

377
00:24:32.906 --> 00:24:35.196
Lion. tiger. hippo. you name it.

378
00:24:36.286 --> 00:24:37.946
You sell them to zoos?

379
00:24:38.076 --> 00:24:39.616
Zoo. circus.

380
00:24:39.956 --> 00:24:42.536
Skipper get big
money for rare animal.

381
00:24:42.706 --> 00:24:45.790
Careful. Camel have
bad accident on floor.

382
00:24:46.000 --> 00:24:47.630
Stain unremovable.

383
00:24:50.840 --> 00:24:53.260
Skipper catch any
wild animal you want.

384
00:24:53.380 --> 00:24:55.220
He'll do you real good
price on white rhino.

385
00:24:55.340 --> 00:24:56.390
Choy.

386
00:24:58.720 --> 00:25:02.060
My apologies for not being
able to offer you a cabin.

387
00:25:02.180 --> 00:25:04.930
Have you found an
enclosure to your taste?

388
00:25:06.190 --> 00:25:07.480
Spoiled for choice.

389
00:25:07.600 --> 00:25:10.274
What are you. Mr Driscoll? A lion?

390
00:25:11.364 --> 00:25:13.074
Or a chimpanzee?

391
00:25:14.574 --> 00:25:16.154
I'll take this one.

392
00:25:29.164 --> 00:25:30.794
I told you to lock it up.

393
00:25:30.914 --> 00:25:34.388
- Sorry. Skipper. Lumpy said-
- Lumpy doesn't give the orders!

394
00:25:34.508 --> 00:25:37.508
What are you trying to do?
Put the whole ship to sleep?

395
00:25:40.888 --> 00:25:42.638
Get them out of here.

396
00:26:17.752 --> 00:26:20.636
- Compliments of the chef.
- Okay.

397
00:26:26.056 --> 00:26:28.056
Oh. Christ. Oh. God.

398
00:26:28.646 --> 00:26:30.936
Lamb's brains in walnut sauce.

399
00:26:36.646 --> 00:26:37.776
Jimmy.

400
00:26:38.026 --> 00:26:39.946
You run those ropes up
on deck like I told you?

401
00:26:40.066 --> 00:26:42.026
Doing it now. Mr Hayes.

402
00:26:42.366 --> 00:26:46.250
How about you return
Mr Driscoll's pen first?

403
00:26:54.080 --> 00:26:55.920
He don't mean no harm.

404
00:26:56.840 --> 00:26:57.920
Thanks.

405
00:26:58.050 --> 00:26:59.760
- I'll keep him out of your way.
- It's okay.

406
00:26:59.880 --> 00:27:02.340
It's just that he
likes it down here.

407
00:27:02.470 --> 00:27:05.010
It's where I found
him four years ago.

408
00:27:05.390 --> 00:27:07.934
Stowed away in one
of them back cages.

409
00:27:09.264 --> 00:27:11.644
His arm was broken in two places.

410
00:27:12.894 --> 00:27:15.734
He was wilder than half
the animals in here.

411
00:27:16.644 --> 00:27:19.234
Still won't tell me
where he came from.

412
00:27:20.444 --> 00:27:22.524
But it wasn't anyplace good.

413
00:27:25.234 --> 00:27:27.194
You got to straighten up.

414
00:27:27.494 --> 00:27:28.614
Jimmy.

415
00:27:29.494 --> 00:27:32.458
You don't want to be on this
ship the rest of your life.

416
00:27:32.578 --> 00:27:34.878
- Yes. I do.
- No. you don't. Jimmy.

417
00:27:35.128 --> 00:27:37.458
You got to be smart.
Get yourself educated.

418
00:27:37.588 --> 00:27:39.458
Give yourself some options.
Take this seriously!

419
00:27:39.588 --> 00:27:41.628
I do. Mr Hayes. I do. Look.

420
00:27:41.838 --> 00:27:43.298
I've been reading.

421
00:27:46.258 --> 00:27:47.928
Where'd you get this?

422
00:27:48.308 --> 00:27:49.558
I borrowed it.

423
00:27:52.848 --> 00:27:54.692
On long-term loan.

424
00:27:55.232 --> 00:27:56.652
Look at this. Look. look.

425
00:27:56.772 --> 00:27:59.982
"Adventures on a tramp
steamer. " See? Just like us.

426
00:28:07.072 --> 00:28:09.662
It's so nice to
meet you. Mr Driscoll.

427
00:28:10.412 --> 00:28:13.242
I'm actually quite familiar
with your work. yes.

428
00:28:17.252 --> 00:28:20.376
Hello. Mr Driscoll.
It's so nice to meet you.

429
00:28:20.546 --> 00:28:23.426
Actually. I'm quite
familiar with your work.

430
00:28:24.136 --> 00:28:25.716
I'm a huge fan.

431
00:28:25.846 --> 00:28:27.716
I've read everything
you've ever written.

432
00:28:27.846 --> 00:28:29.266
No. too much.

433
00:28:30.016 --> 00:28:33.226
Gonna have the ship's
engines all over the dialogue.

434
00:28:34.016 --> 00:28:35.306
Seagulls.

435
00:28:36.396 --> 00:28:38.476
Camera noise. Wind.
Christ knows what else.

436
00:28:38.606 --> 00:28:39.686
I don't care. Mike.

437
00:28:39.816 --> 00:28:42.190
You're the sound
recordist. Make it work.

438
00:28:43.690 --> 00:28:46.450
Ann! Come on in. Let me
introduce you to the crew.

439
00:28:46.570 --> 00:28:48.700
This is Herb. the cameraman.

440
00:28:49.320 --> 00:28:51.990
- Delighted to meet you. ma'am.
- Likewise.

441
00:28:52.120 --> 00:28:54.200
May I say what a lovely dress?

442
00:28:54.330 --> 00:28:57.160
Oh. this old thing?
I just threw it on.

443
00:28:57.700 --> 00:29:00.210
Isn't that one of
Maureen's costumes?

444
00:29:00.620 --> 00:29:04.340
Now. what does a girl have to do
around here to get some breakfast?

445
00:29:04.460 --> 00:29:06.424
Lumpy. you heard the lady.

446
00:29:06.554 --> 00:29:09.964
Fancy my porridge à la walnuts?

447
00:29:14.094 --> 00:29:16.684
Oh. Ann. I don't
believe you've met...

448
00:29:19.144 --> 00:29:20.184
Ann?

449
00:29:20.684 --> 00:29:23.814
That's all right. Mr
Denham. I know who this is.

450
00:29:29.114 --> 00:29:32.698
Thrilled to meet you. It's an
honour to be a part of this.

451
00:29:33.988 --> 00:29:35.368
Gee. thanks.

452
00:29:35.998 --> 00:29:38.868
Actually. I'm quite
familiar with your work.

453
00:29:39.328 --> 00:29:40.498
Really?

454
00:29:41.328 --> 00:29:43.378
Yes. and what I most admire...

455
00:29:43.498 --> 00:29:47.048
is the way you've captured
the voice of the common people.

456
00:29:48.338 --> 00:29:50.088
Well. that's my job.

457
00:29:53.052 --> 00:29:55.342
I'm sure you've heard
this before. Mr Driscoll...

458
00:29:55.472 --> 00:29:56.892
if you don't mind me saying...

459
00:29:57.012 --> 00:30:00.022
but you don't look at
all like your photograph.

460
00:30:05.192 --> 00:30:06.852
- Excuse me. - Wait
a minute. Ann-

461
00:30:06.982 --> 00:30:09.732
He's so much younger in
person. And much better-looking.

462
00:30:09.862 --> 00:30:11.402
Ann. stop. Stop right there.

463
00:30:11.522 --> 00:30:13.652
You see. I was just
afraid that you might be...

464
00:30:13.782 --> 00:30:16.532
one of those self-obsessed
literary types.

465
00:30:17.076 --> 00:30:18.406
- I'm sorry. I'm
not- -You know...

466
00:30:18.536 --> 00:30:22.246
the tweedy twerp with his nose
in his book and his head up his-

467
00:30:26.456 --> 00:30:29.126
It's nice to meet
you. too. Miss Darrow.

468
00:30:43.060 --> 00:30:44.440
Good Christ!

469
00:31:10.964 --> 00:31:14.464
She's standing at the
railing. She doesn't know it yet...

470
00:31:15.754 --> 00:31:19.214
but they are sailing towards
disaster. You got that?

471
00:31:19.424 --> 00:31:21.134
Okay. so she turns...

472
00:31:22.474 --> 00:31:24.304
the first mate is
staggering towards her.

473
00:31:25.724 --> 00:31:28.268
There's a knife
sticking out of his back.

474
00:31:28.398 --> 00:31:31.278
Wait a sec. We're killing
off the first mate?

475
00:31:31.858 --> 00:31:33.988
That's assuming she knows
who the first mate is.

476
00:31:34.108 --> 00:31:36.908
Come on. Jack. It
was an honest mistake.

477
00:31:37.028 --> 00:31:39.528
Ann is nearsighted. It could
have happened to anyone.

478
00:31:39.658 --> 00:31:41.198
I was joking. Carl.

479
00:31:41.328 --> 00:31:44.578
The point is. she's horrified.
She has to look away.

480
00:31:47.328 --> 00:31:49.418
And that's when she sees it.

481
00:31:51.632 --> 00:31:52.962
Sees what?

482
00:31:54.252 --> 00:31:55.342
What?

483
00:32:00.882 --> 00:32:02.222
The island.

484
00:32:05.852 --> 00:32:10.182
We're filming on an island
now? When did this happen?

485
00:32:11.102 --> 00:32:13.522
Jack. keep your voice down.

486
00:32:14.022 --> 00:32:16.566
I don't want the
crew getting spooked.

487
00:32:17.196 --> 00:32:20.196
Why would they get
spooked? What's it called?

488
00:32:20.326 --> 00:32:22.286
All right. It has a local name...

489
00:32:22.406 --> 00:32:24.866
but I'm warning you. Jack.
it doesn't sound good.

490
00:32:24.996 --> 00:32:27.656
They call it Skull Island.

491
00:32:27.826 --> 00:32:29.456
Did you get that?

492
00:32:30.286 --> 00:32:31.576
What's wrong with this place?

493
00:32:31.706 --> 00:32:34.376
There's nothing
officially wrong with it.

494
00:32:34.626 --> 00:32:37.956
Because. technically. it
hasn't been discovered yet.

495
00:32:40.420 --> 00:32:42.340
Okay. All right.

496
00:32:44.590 --> 00:32:46.810
So we arrive at this place.

497
00:32:47.430 --> 00:32:48.600
S...

498
00:32:49.270 --> 00:32:50.430
K...

499
00:32:51.520 --> 00:32:52.850
U...

500
00:32:53.890 --> 00:32:55.060
L...

501
00:32:56.600 --> 00:32:57.810
L...

502
00:33:03.324 --> 00:33:04.654
Island.

503
00:33:08.994 --> 00:33:12.084
All right. everyone.
from the top! And action!

504
00:33:13.664 --> 00:33:17.294
I think this is awfully exciting!
I've never been on a ship before.

505
00:33:17.414 --> 00:33:19.964
And I've never been on
one with a woman before.

506
00:33:20.084 --> 00:33:23.504
I guess you don't think much
of women on ships. do you?

507
00:33:23.924 --> 00:33:25.544
No. they're a nuisance.

508
00:33:25.674 --> 00:33:29.268
- Well. I'll try not to be.
- Just being around is trouble.

509
00:33:37.608 --> 00:33:38.608
Cut!

510
00:33:39.768 --> 00:33:41.108
It's great.

511
00:33:41.278 --> 00:33:45.448
Bruce. wonderful performance.
You can relax for 10 minutes.

512
00:33:45.568 --> 00:33:48.448
That was very natural. I felt moved.

513
00:33:48.618 --> 00:33:52.082
What do you think. Driscoll?
Dialogue's got some flow now. huh?

514
00:33:52.202 --> 00:33:53.952
It was pure effluence.

515
00:33:54.082 --> 00:33:55.792
I beefed up the banter.

516
00:33:55.912 --> 00:33:58.002
Try to resist that impulse.

517
00:33:58.662 --> 00:34:00.292
It's just a little
bit of humour. bud.

518
00:34:00.422 --> 00:34:02.832
What are you. a
Bolshevik or something?

519
00:34:02.962 --> 00:34:04.132
Actors.

520
00:34:05.302 --> 00:34:08.552
Travel the world. but all
they ever see is a mirror.

521
00:34:21.066 --> 00:34:22.356
Good legs.

522
00:34:24.066 --> 00:34:26.606
Sea legs. Well. you know. sea legs.

523
00:34:29.196 --> 00:34:30.196
Yeah.

524
00:34:30.326 --> 00:34:33.906
Not that you don't have good
legs. Just making conversation.

525
00:34:34.036 --> 00:34:36.286
Jesus. Miss Darrow!

526
00:34:38.290 --> 00:34:40.790
About the scene today
with you and Bruce-

527
00:34:40.920 --> 00:34:42.670
I know it wasn't what you wrote...

528
00:34:42.790 --> 00:34:46.800
but Mr Baxter felt very strongly
that when a man likes a woman...

529
00:34:47.460 --> 00:34:49.090
he must ignore her.

530
00:34:49.220 --> 00:34:52.010
And if things turn
really hostile. then...

531
00:34:52.930 --> 00:34:54.090
No?

532
00:34:54.220 --> 00:34:55.890
Interesting theory.

533
00:34:56.640 --> 00:34:58.640
I know. I should have...

534
00:34:58.810 --> 00:35:01.020
It wasn't what I
had intended. but-

535
00:35:01.140 --> 00:35:02.604
I'm sorry. I was...

536
00:35:02.734 --> 00:35:04.694
And you made it your own.

537
00:35:05.694 --> 00:35:07.154
I was nervous.

538
00:35:07.404 --> 00:35:09.984
It was funny. actually.
You were funny.

539
00:35:10.944 --> 00:35:13.194
Please don't say
another word. Good night.

540
00:35:13.324 --> 00:35:14.694
Miss Darrow.

541
00:35:20.374 --> 00:35:22.534
You don't have to be nervous.

542
00:36:33.106 --> 00:36:34.396
Thank you.

543
00:36:35.316 --> 00:36:36.950
Let's take it...

544
00:36:37.070 --> 00:36:39.320
Would you please... We're
trying to shoot a scene.

545
00:36:39.450 --> 00:36:41.030
- Okay.
- Thank you.

546
00:36:41.490 --> 00:36:42.580
Okay. again.

547
00:36:57.170 --> 00:36:59.300
We're close. Turn southwest.

548
00:36:59.840 --> 00:37:02.974
There's no land southwest
for thousands of miles.

549
00:37:04.934 --> 00:37:07.434
It takes us way outside
the shipping lanes.

550
00:37:07.564 --> 00:37:09.974
I won't sail blind in these waters.

551
00:37:11.064 --> 00:37:13.274
I'll make it worth your while.

552
00:37:14.604 --> 00:37:16.604
There's nothing out there.

553
00:37:17.364 --> 00:37:19.734
Well. then you've nothing to lose.

554
00:37:31.838 --> 00:37:35.758
If someone were to tell you this
ship was headed for Singapore...

555
00:37:37.258 --> 00:37:38.968
what would you say?

556
00:37:39.088 --> 00:37:41.838
I would say they're
full of it. Mr Hayes.

557
00:37:43.848 --> 00:37:46.348
Well. we turned
southwest last night.

558
00:37:46.558 --> 00:37:48.182
Gentlemen. please.

559
00:37:49.682 --> 00:37:52.142
- We're not looking for trouble.
- No.

560
00:37:53.522 --> 00:37:55.852
You're looking for something else.

561
00:37:59.272 --> 00:38:00.652
Yes. we are.

562
00:38:02.362 --> 00:38:04.702
We're going to find Skull Island.

563
00:38:05.322 --> 00:38:08.112
Find it. film it. and
show it to the world.

564
00:38:09.162 --> 00:38:12.876
For 25 cents. you get to see
the last blank space on the map.

565
00:38:13.336 --> 00:38:15.506
I wouldn't be so sure of that.

566
00:38:17.836 --> 00:38:19.426
What do you mean?

567
00:38:20.216 --> 00:38:22.756
Seven years ago. me and Mr
Hayes were working our passage...

568
00:38:22.886 --> 00:38:24.386
on a Norwegian bark.

569
00:38:24.506 --> 00:38:27.306
We picked up a castaway.
We found him in the water.

570
00:38:27.596 --> 00:38:29.386
He'd been drifting for days.

571
00:38:29.516 --> 00:38:32.886
His ship had run aground on
an island way west of Sumatra.

572
00:38:33.016 --> 00:38:36.400
An island hidden in fog.

573
00:38:38.230 --> 00:38:40.440
He spoke of a huge wall...

574
00:38:41.780 --> 00:38:43.490
built so long ago...

575
00:38:44.030 --> 00:38:46.030
no one knew who'd made it.

576
00:38:46.280 --> 00:38:49.160
A wall 100 foot high...

577
00:38:49.450 --> 00:38:52.240
as strong today as it was ages ago.

578
00:38:54.080 --> 00:38:56.040
Why'd they build the wall?

579
00:39:00.504 --> 00:39:04.134
Well. the castaway. he
spoke of a creature...

580
00:39:04.594 --> 00:39:06.674
neither beast nor man...

581
00:39:07.214 --> 00:39:10.434
but something monstrous.
living behind that wall.

582
00:39:11.264 --> 00:39:12.844
A lion or a tiger.

583
00:39:13.844 --> 00:39:16.104
A man-eater. That's how
all these stories start.

584
00:39:16.224 --> 00:39:17.974
What else did he say?

585
00:39:18.354 --> 00:39:19.434
Nothing.

586
00:39:19.564 --> 00:39:23.238
We found him the next morning. He'd
stuck a knife through his heart.

587
00:39:23.818 --> 00:39:26.868
Sorry. fellows. You'll
have to do better than that.

588
00:39:28.118 --> 00:39:30.368
Monsters belong in B movies.

589
00:39:30.488 --> 00:39:32.448
If you find this place...

590
00:39:32.998 --> 00:39:36.408
if you go ashore with your
friends and your cameras...

591
00:39:37.618 --> 00:39:39.248
you won't come back.

592
00:39:40.288 --> 00:39:42.748
Just as long as you understand that.

593
00:41:02.664 --> 00:41:05.504
How long do you expect
us to stay out here?

594
00:41:11.134 --> 00:41:13.344
You're writing a stage comedy?

595
00:41:13.504 --> 00:41:15.344
I'm writing it for you.

596
00:41:17.554 --> 00:41:19.384
Why would you do that?

597
00:41:20.384 --> 00:41:23.188
- Why would I write a play for you?
- Yes.

598
00:41:24.898 --> 00:41:26.478
Isn't it obvious?

599
00:41:29.228 --> 00:41:30.528
Not to me.

600
00:41:34.408 --> 00:41:35.568
Well...

601
00:41:37.158 --> 00:41:38.908
it's in the subtext.

602
00:41:41.698 --> 00:41:43.868
I guess I must have missed it.

603
00:41:49.042 --> 00:41:50.792
It's not about words.

604
00:42:33.960 --> 00:42:35.920
Message for you. Captain.

605
00:42:54.350 --> 00:42:55.944
What's going on?

606
00:42:56.774 --> 00:42:59.574
Hayes. why are we changing course?

607
00:43:01.154 --> 00:43:03.404
- Englehorn. you
can't just- -Outside.

608
00:43:07.494 --> 00:43:10.084
There's a warrant
out for your arrest.

609
00:43:10.454 --> 00:43:12.044
Did you know that?

610
00:43:14.504 --> 00:43:17.084
I've been ordered
to divert to Rangoon.

611
00:43:21.298 --> 00:43:24.598
Another week. I
haven't got a film yet.

612
00:43:25.928 --> 00:43:28.638
Please. I have risked
everything I have on this.

613
00:43:28.768 --> 00:43:31.978
No. Denham. You risked
everything I have.

614
00:43:33.938 --> 00:43:35.148
What do you want?

615
00:43:35.268 --> 00:43:37.478
Tell me what you want.
I'll give you anything.

616
00:43:37.608 --> 00:43:39.478
I want you off my ship.

617
00:43:42.068 --> 00:43:44.572
Set a course for Rangoon. Mr Hayes.

618
00:43:51.202 --> 00:43:52.622
I'm finished.

619
00:43:54.162 --> 00:43:55.962
It's over for me. Jack.

620
00:43:57.752 --> 00:44:00.212
How'd you think
this would end. Carl?

621
00:44:15.976 --> 00:44:19.356
Check our position. Use the stars.

622
00:44:33.040 --> 00:44:35.160
There are no stars. Captain.

623
00:44:37.620 --> 00:44:39.000
What is that?

624
00:44:41.000 --> 00:44:43.050
- What?
- That.

625
00:44:47.050 --> 00:44:48.680
That right there.

626
00:44:49.760 --> 00:44:52.510
I don't know. What
is it? A coffee stain?

627
00:46:30.860 --> 00:46:34.660
Station the forward lookout and
get me the depth by lead line.

628
00:46:34.990 --> 00:46:36.450
Aye. Captain.

629
00:46:47.790 --> 00:46:49.880
30 fathoms. no bottom!

630
00:46:51.750 --> 00:46:54.674
Reduce speed. steerage way only.

631
00:46:55.514 --> 00:46:57.304
Dead slow ahead. both.

632
00:47:00.394 --> 00:47:02.354
You should stop the ship.

633
00:47:03.764 --> 00:47:05.514
15 degrees port.

634
00:47:08.434 --> 00:47:10.144
We're getting out of here. Mr Hayes.

635
00:47:10.274 --> 00:47:12.314
We'll find clear conditions.

636
00:47:13.024 --> 00:47:14.524
We have seabed!

637
00:47:20.328 --> 00:47:21.788
25 fathoms!

638
00:47:23.708 --> 00:47:25.118
We're shallowing!

639
00:47:25.248 --> 00:47:26.538
20 degrees starboard!

640
00:47:26.668 --> 00:47:28.668
Captain. you don't know
where the hell you're going!

641
00:47:28.788 --> 00:47:30.378
Get me another reading!

642
00:47:33.668 --> 00:47:35.218
Another reading!

643
00:47:37.798 --> 00:47:39.508
22 fathoms!

644
00:47:41.052 --> 00:47:43.102
- Douse the lights.
- Aye. Captain.

645
00:47:55.152 --> 00:47:56.522
10 fathoms!

646
00:48:08.126 --> 00:48:10.876
Wall! There's a wall ahead!

647
00:48:28.180 --> 00:48:29.640
Stop engines!

648
00:49:32.998 --> 00:49:34.748
Give me some power!
Half astern both.

649
00:49:34.868 --> 00:49:36.918
Half astern both. Captain!

650
00:49:41.502 --> 00:49:42.672
Rocks!

651
00:49:45.842 --> 00:49:46.972
Rocks!

652
00:49:51.552 --> 00:49:53.682
Rocks to starboard. Captain!

653
00:49:54.222 --> 00:49:56.562
To port! Rocks everywhere!

654
00:49:56.772 --> 00:49:58.312
Take the wheel. Hayes.

655
00:50:15.536 --> 00:50:16.706
Hang on!

656
00:50:40.230 --> 00:50:41.520
Full ahead!

657
00:50:47.400 --> 00:50:49.240
Rocks to port. Captain!

658
00:50:50.240 --> 00:50:52.994
Turn. Captain!
Starboard. starboard!

659
00:52:20.446 --> 00:52:21.996
Shore up that breach!

660
00:52:22.116 --> 00:52:25.750
Get me more men down here
now! Come on. move. move!

661
00:52:27.420 --> 00:52:29.670
- Hayes!
- She's taken a pounding!

662
00:52:31.960 --> 00:52:33.380
What about the prop?

663
00:52:33.510 --> 00:52:35.630
The shaft's not bent.
as far as we can tell.

664
00:52:35.760 --> 00:52:37.930
But she struck hard
against the rock!

665
00:52:38.970 --> 00:52:40.180
Captain!

666
00:52:40.890 --> 00:52:42.600
Better come up quick!

667
00:52:44.520 --> 00:52:45.890
Right there!

668
00:53:00.744 --> 00:53:02.784
Want me to bring them back?

669
00:53:03.494 --> 00:53:05.124
I don't give a damn
about Carl Denham.

670
00:53:05.244 --> 00:53:08.704
I want this ship fixed and ready
to float on the next high tide!

671
00:53:08.834 --> 00:53:10.414
Come on. move it.

672
00:53:11.624 --> 00:53:13.588
We're leaving. Mr Hayes.

673
00:53:21.008 --> 00:53:23.098
Can you believe this. Jack?

674
00:53:26.428 --> 00:53:28.268
We've got our picture.

675
00:54:25.910 --> 00:54:28.580
Why does Marlow keep
going up the river?

676
00:54:30.000 --> 00:54:31.960
Why doesn't he turn back?

677
00:54:34.420 --> 00:54:37.210
There's a part of him
that wants to. Jimmy.

678
00:54:38.590 --> 00:54:41.710
A part deep inside himself
that sounds a warning.

679
00:54:43.590 --> 00:54:45.630
But there's another part...

680
00:54:46.800 --> 00:54:48.514
that needs to know.

681
00:54:51.764 --> 00:54:54.564
To defeat the thing
which makes him afraid.

682
00:54:56.524 --> 00:54:59.774
"We could not understand
because we were too far...

683
00:55:00.694 --> 00:55:01.854
"and could not remember...

684
00:55:01.984 --> 00:55:05.444
"because we were travelling
in the night of first ages...

685
00:55:06.324 --> 00:55:08.574
"of those ages that are gone...

686
00:55:09.824 --> 00:55:12.498
"leaving hardly a
sign. and no memories.

687
00:55:15.418 --> 00:55:16.588
"We are accustomed to look...

688
00:55:16.708 --> 00:55:19.838
"upon the shackled form
of a conquered monster...

689
00:55:22.338 --> 00:55:23.798
"but there...

690
00:55:25.218 --> 00:55:28.928
"there you could look at a
thing monstrous and free."

691
00:55:38.982 --> 00:55:41.192
It's not an adventure story...

692
00:55:41.812 --> 00:55:43.402
is it. Mr Hayes?

693
00:55:45.442 --> 00:55:46.732
No. Jimmy.

694
00:55:47.862 --> 00:55:49.242
It's not.

695
00:56:11.756 --> 00:56:14.136
- It's deserted.
- Of course it's deserted.

696
00:56:14.266 --> 00:56:17.636
Use your eyes. Preston.
The place is a ruin.

697
00:56:19.096 --> 00:56:21.856
Nobody's lived here
for hundreds of years.

698
00:57:35.762 --> 00:57:38.222
Mr Denham. I think
we should go back.

699
00:57:38.342 --> 00:57:40.052
I will handle this.

700
00:57:45.522 --> 00:57:47.102
Look. Chocolate.

701
00:57:48.392 --> 00:57:50.062
You like chocolate?

702
00:57:52.902 --> 00:57:54.522
It's good to eat.

703
00:57:56.902 --> 00:57:58.156
You want?

704
00:58:04.206 --> 00:58:05.376
Take it.

705
00:58:13.166 --> 00:58:15.506
Here. put it in your
hand and take it.

706
00:58:21.600 --> 00:58:24.020
For God's sakes. Denham.
leave the native alone.

707
00:58:24.140 --> 00:58:26.390
She doesn't want the chocolate.

708
00:58:51.624 --> 00:58:52.964
All right!

709
00:58:53.374 --> 00:58:55.834
Just a bunch of women and old folks!

710
00:58:57.674 --> 00:58:59.254
They're harmless!

711
01:00:21.050 --> 01:00:22.050
Ann!

712
01:01:49.592 --> 01:01:50.632
Jack.

713
01:02:04.896 --> 01:02:06.276
Seen enough?

714
01:02:14.156 --> 01:02:15.786
Lighten the ship!

715
01:02:16.326 --> 01:02:19.960
Anything that's not
bolted down goes overboard!

716
01:02:22.330 --> 01:02:23.790
Just heave it!

717
01:02:24.330 --> 01:02:25.540
We got away.

718
01:02:25.670 --> 01:02:27.340
We gotta be grateful
for that. gentlemen.

719
01:02:27.460 --> 01:02:31.170
What about Mike? He didn't
get away! He's still there!

720
01:02:31.920 --> 01:02:35.180
Mike died doing what he believed
in! He didn't die for nothing.

721
01:02:35.300 --> 01:02:39.300
And I'll tell you something else.
I'm gonna finish this film for Mike!

722
01:02:45.814 --> 01:02:47.394
I'll finish it...

723
01:02:49.354 --> 01:02:51.614
and I'll donate the proceeds...

724
01:02:52.364 --> 01:02:54.114
to his wife and kids.

725
01:02:54.574 --> 01:02:58.114
Because that man is a hero.
and he deserves nothing less.

726
01:02:58.994 --> 01:03:00.324
Hear. hear!

727
01:03:38.862 --> 01:03:41.202
Chuck everything
except for the potatoes!

728
01:03:46.792 --> 01:03:49.582
- What's wrong now?
- Excuse me. Shakespeare.

729
01:03:50.122 --> 01:03:52.462
Come on.
men! Come on. hurry!

730
01:04:03.766 --> 01:04:07.096
Drop those spare cables
overboard! Go on. just chuck it!

731
01:04:25.580 --> 01:04:26.700
- Where's Ann?
- What?

732
01:04:26.830 --> 01:04:27.910
Where's Ann?

733
01:04:33.330 --> 01:04:34.420
Ann!

734
01:04:54.144 --> 01:04:55.434
She's free!

735
01:05:01.824 --> 01:05:04.364
Full ahead. both engines!

736
01:05:11.668 --> 01:05:13.078
Ann!

737
01:05:35.192 --> 01:05:38.562
No! Stop! Turn back!

738
01:05:39.942 --> 01:05:41.152
Stop!

739
01:05:43.072 --> 01:05:44.822
We have to turn back.

740
01:05:45.072 --> 01:05:46.692
They've taken Ann.

741
01:05:53.376 --> 01:05:54.536
No!

742
01:05:59.166 --> 01:06:02.216
Kong! Kong! Kong!

743
01:06:44.424 --> 01:06:48.304
All hands going ashore!
Report to stations!

744
01:06:49.634 --> 01:06:52.054
Jump to it! Jump to it. gentlemen!

745
01:06:55.764 --> 01:06:57.434
We're doing it. Mr Hayes!

746
01:07:04.778 --> 01:07:06.528
Come on. move it!

747
01:07:23.578 --> 01:07:25.208
Pull harder!

748
01:07:26.588 --> 01:07:28.422
Row! Row!

749
01:07:28.672 --> 01:07:29.842
Come on!

750
01:08:16.680 --> 01:08:17.810
Kong.

751
01:10:40.194 --> 01:10:41.944
Spread out! Find her!

752
01:10:50.824 --> 01:10:52.164
Miss Darrow!

753
01:10:52.374 --> 01:10:55.164
- Check up there. Jimmy!
- Everybody stay together!

754
01:10:58.624 --> 01:10:59.624
Ann!

755
01:11:01.798 --> 01:11:03.508
She's here somewhere!

756
01:11:08.258 --> 01:11:10.058
What in God's name was that?

757
01:11:16.478 --> 01:11:18.018
Behind the wall!

758
01:11:18.808 --> 01:11:20.358
Behind the wall!

759
01:12:12.080 --> 01:12:13.410
She's gone!

760
01:12:24.420 --> 01:12:26.130
Carl. what is it?

761
01:12:32.800 --> 01:12:34.430
You saw something.

762
01:12:41.644 --> 01:12:44.444
You can take Hayes and 15 others.

763
01:12:45.144 --> 01:12:47.904
I'll put a guard on the
gate until you return.

764
01:12:48.024 --> 01:12:50.444
The rest of you stay with the ship.

765
01:12:50.614 --> 01:12:51.654
Choy!

766
01:12:53.484 --> 01:12:54.994
Not you. Jimmy.

767
01:12:55.154 --> 01:12:57.244
Come on. Mr Hayes. Look at them.

768
01:12:57.364 --> 01:12:59.078
None of them knows
which way to point a gun.

769
01:12:59.208 --> 01:13:00.458
Stay here.

770
01:13:00.998 --> 01:13:03.458
- Miss Darrow needs me!
- No!

771
01:13:08.338 --> 01:13:10.678
Bring the tripod and
all of the film stock.

772
01:13:10.798 --> 01:13:13.178
You wanna go with the 6-inch lens?

773
01:13:13.678 --> 01:13:16.048
The wide-angle will do just fine.

774
01:13:22.098 --> 01:13:24.982
You got guns. You
got food. You got the ammo.

775
01:13:25.522 --> 01:13:27.272
And you got 24 hours!

776
01:13:27.772 --> 01:13:29.152
24 hours?

777
01:13:29.442 --> 01:13:31.572
This time tomorrow. we haul anchor.

778
01:13:55.046 --> 01:13:56.556
Miss Darrow!

779
01:13:58.966 --> 01:14:00.056
Ann!

780
01:14:03.516 --> 01:14:04.846
Miss Darrow!

781
01:14:13.820 --> 01:14:14.610
Miss Darrow!

782
01:14:32.580 --> 01:14:34.214
What is it?

783
01:14:43.974 --> 01:14:45.264
Fire!

784
01:14:47.014 --> 01:14:48.354
Cut it out.

785
01:14:49.564 --> 01:14:51.064
Hold your fire.

786
01:14:51.354 --> 01:14:53.234
Hold your fire!

787
01:15:23.552 --> 01:15:26.432
Stay down. damn it. Stay down.

788
01:15:41.072 --> 01:15:44.692
Come on. Come on. Come on.

789
01:16:16.400 --> 01:16:18.360
Good shooting. Mr Hayes.

790
01:16:22.530 --> 01:16:24.820
Aren't these things
supposed to be extinct?

791
01:16:25.070 --> 01:16:26.490
They are now.

792
01:16:32.240 --> 01:16:34.834
What the hell kind
of a place is this?

793
01:16:50.384 --> 01:16:51.764
Miss Darrow!

794
01:16:56.518 --> 01:16:57.568
Ann!

795
01:18:13.140 --> 01:18:14.260
No!

796
01:18:31.864 --> 01:18:33.994
- Ann!
- Miss Darrow!

797
01:18:42.664 --> 01:18:43.664
Ann!

798
01:18:53.094 --> 01:18:54.174
Ann!

799
01:19:31.172 --> 01:19:33.552
Christ. it's a bleeding boneyard!

800
01:19:34.962 --> 01:19:37.382
They've been ripped limb from limb.

801
01:19:39.262 --> 01:19:41.682
Ann! Ann!

802
01:19:54.946 --> 01:19:57.196
Just keep walking. Mr Hayes.
Pretend you didn't see me.

803
01:19:57.316 --> 01:19:59.236
- Jesus. Jimmy.
- Hey. I need that!

804
01:19:59.366 --> 01:20:00.576
I'm not giving you a gun!

805
01:20:00.696 --> 01:20:02.656
You were younger than me
when they gave you one!

806
01:20:02.786 --> 01:20:06.290
I was in the Army. I was
trained. I had a drill sergeant.

807
01:20:07.790 --> 01:20:09.920
I wanna help bring her back.

808
01:20:17.800 --> 01:20:19.720
Don't make me regret it.

809
01:20:47.175 --> 01:20:49.175
Conserve your ammunition!

810
01:20:58.518 --> 01:21:00.018
I'm knackered.

811
01:21:02.318 --> 01:21:04.400
- I gotta have a breather.
- Great idea.

812
01:21:04.490 --> 01:21:05.950
Fellows. we don't
have time for this.

813
01:21:06.030 --> 01:21:08.452
We've lost too much ground
already. Come on. get up!

814
01:21:08.532 --> 01:21:11.952
They're not about to quit
on you. Cut them some slack.

815
01:21:12.122 --> 01:21:14.453
All right. you got five minutes!

816
01:21:14.663 --> 01:21:16.624
Everybody stay in sight.

817
01:21:20.625 --> 01:21:24.045
Over here. I'm gonna get
a wide shot of the valley.

818
01:21:54.294 --> 01:21:55.664
Bloody Nora!

819
01:22:02.796 --> 01:22:05.007
Is that what took Miss Darrow?

820
01:22:08.598 --> 01:22:12.730
There's only one creature capable
of leaving a footprint that size.

821
01:22:19.190 --> 01:22:21.071
The abominable snowman.

822
01:22:22.692 --> 01:22:25.363
- Yeah. a snowman.
- We dead meat.

823
01:22:26.073 --> 01:22:28.493
It's got to be what. 20. 25 feet?

824
01:22:30.583 --> 01:22:32.034
Carl saw it.

825
01:22:33.415 --> 01:22:34.915
Let's ask him.

826
01:22:37.046 --> 01:22:38.257
Denham!

827
01:22:40.798 --> 01:22:42.088
Where'd he go?

828
01:23:02.283 --> 01:23:04.073
Walk forward. Bruce.

829
01:23:04.613 --> 01:23:06.414
- What?
- You're the star of this picture.

830
01:23:06.494 --> 01:23:09.534
Get into character and
head toward the animals.

831
01:23:15.668 --> 01:23:18.299
What the hell kind
of a place is this?

832
01:23:28.482 --> 01:23:30.812
Are you sure about this. Denham?

833
01:23:31.312 --> 01:23:33.402
Don't we have a stand-in
for this type of thing?

834
01:23:33.482 --> 01:23:36.402
I need you in the shot. or
people will say they're fake.

835
01:23:36.482 --> 01:23:38.652
Nobody's gonna think these are fake.

836
01:23:47.326 --> 01:23:49.336
You're making them nervous.
No sudden movements.

837
01:23:49.416 --> 01:23:50.707
I'm not moving.

838
01:23:56.509 --> 01:23:58.839
Mother of God.

839
01:24:20.786 --> 01:24:22.156
What's this?

840
01:24:48.394 --> 01:24:49.854
What is it? What
is it? Where's Carl?

841
01:24:49.944 --> 01:24:52.734
Carl? He's up there. filming.

842
01:25:03.167 --> 01:25:04.577
Bugger this!

843
01:25:05.327 --> 01:25:06.667
Watch out.

844
01:25:11.960 --> 01:25:13.300
Run. Jack!

845
01:25:16.590 --> 01:25:19.091
- Holy Christ.
- Go. Jimmy. run!

846
01:25:20.012 --> 01:25:21.513
Run. run. run!

847
01:25:28.395 --> 01:25:29.985
- Let go!
- I'm not leaving the camera!

848
01:25:30.065 --> 01:25:31.356
Let go. you idiot!

849
01:25:31.446 --> 01:25:33.276
Carl. run!

850
01:25:46.709 --> 01:25:47.959
Look out!

851
01:25:48.799 --> 01:25:49.840
Look out!

852
01:26:40.144 --> 01:26:41.686
Coming through!

853
01:27:45.964 --> 01:27:47.004
No!

854
01:27:47.714 --> 01:27:48.964
Come on.

855
01:28:30.135 --> 01:28:32.845
Carl! Carl!

856
01:28:36.017 --> 01:28:38.568
Get up! Come on. Come on.

857
01:28:53.373 --> 01:28:56.043
Mr Denham! Mr Denham!

858
01:28:56.753 --> 01:28:59.373
Herb! Herb. come on!

859
01:28:59.463 --> 01:29:01.173
Take the tripod!

860
01:29:01.383 --> 01:29:02.635
Come on!

861
01:29:03.845 --> 01:29:06.386
I'm pulling you up!
Hold on to your end!

862
01:29:06.466 --> 01:29:07.516
Go!

863
01:29:07.596 --> 01:29:09.267
No. I'm not going
anywhere without you!

864
01:29:09.927 --> 01:29:12.597
- You gotta leave me!
- Shut up and hold on!

865
01:30:20.348 --> 01:30:22.098
Jimmy. do a head count.

866
01:30:22.178 --> 01:30:24.678
I want to know how many
are injured and how bad.

867
01:30:24.768 --> 01:30:26.018
Injured?

868
01:30:27.428 --> 01:30:29.188
Four of us are dead!

869
01:30:35.901 --> 01:30:37.651
It's not your fault.

870
01:30:38.111 --> 01:30:40.821
What happened to Herb
is no one's fault.

871
01:30:41.281 --> 01:30:43.663
You're absolutely right. Preston.

872
01:30:44.073 --> 01:30:46.494
And I'll tell you something else.

873
01:30:46.574 --> 01:30:48.834
Herbert didn't die for nothing.

874
01:30:49.244 --> 01:30:52.046
He died for what he believed
in. and I'm gonna honour that.

875
01:30:52.126 --> 01:30:56.177
He died believing there was still
some mystery left in this world.

876
01:30:56.677 --> 01:30:59.258
And we could all
have a piece of it...

877
01:30:59.468 --> 01:31:02.008
for the price of
an admission ticket.

878
01:31:02.218 --> 01:31:05.929
God damn it. Preston. we're
gonna finish this film for Herb.

879
01:31:06.349 --> 01:31:08.020
We'll finish it...

880
01:31:08.100 --> 01:31:11.021
and donate the proceeds
to his wife and kids.

881
01:31:18.363 --> 01:31:20.533
Come on. guys. We need more rope.

882
01:31:22.453 --> 01:31:24.455
All right. we gotta
get back to the ship.

883
01:31:24.535 --> 01:31:28.206
- Englehorn sails in nine hours.
- So? We gotta find Miss Darrow.

884
01:31:28.296 --> 01:31:30.916
Hey. do you hear me? We're
gonna be stranded here.

885
01:31:32.757 --> 01:31:36.177
Miss Darrow was a
great gal. no question.

886
01:31:36.638 --> 01:31:38.389
And she was a wonderful person.

887
01:31:38.469 --> 01:31:41.680
It's a terrible loss and
we're all gonna miss her.

888
01:31:41.970 --> 01:31:45.891
I always knew you were nothing like
the tough guy you play on screen.

889
01:31:45.981 --> 01:31:47.691
I just never figured
you for a coward.

890
01:31:47.771 --> 01:31:49.903
Hey. pal! Hey. wake up.

891
01:31:50.403 --> 01:31:52.903
Heroes don't look like
me. not in the real world.

892
01:31:52.983 --> 01:31:56.533
In the real world. they got bad
teeth. a bald spot. and a beer gut.

893
01:31:56.613 --> 01:32:00.115
I'm just an actor with a gun.
who's lost his motivation.

894
01:32:01.575 --> 01:32:03.076
Be seeing you.

895
01:32:04.286 --> 01:32:05.666
Anyone else?

896
01:32:07.206 --> 01:32:09.166
- Well. see you.
- Come on.

897
01:37:05.911 --> 01:37:07.121
No!

898
01:37:07.782 --> 01:37:09.242
I said no!

899
01:37:16.714 --> 01:37:20.465
That's all there is.
There isn't any more.

900
01:39:42.704 --> 01:39:45.495
Get them off the
boat. Get them off the boat.

901
01:39:47.877 --> 01:39:49.257
Keep paddling.

902
01:40:26.417 --> 01:40:28.338
What the hell was that?

903
01:41:09.379 --> 01:41:11.759
Come on. Get
them out of there!

904
01:41:13.549 --> 01:41:14.891
Preston!

905
01:41:20.023 --> 01:41:21.683
Give me your hand.

906
01:41:22.273 --> 01:41:23.483
Jack!

907
01:41:28.946 --> 01:41:30.236
Jack!

908
01:41:35.037 --> 01:41:36.327
- Choy!
- Help!

909
01:41:36.417 --> 01:41:38.458
Swim. you filthy bugger.

910
01:42:47.448 --> 01:42:48.948
Choy!

911
01:42:50.748 --> 01:42:51.868
Stay with him.

912
01:42:51.948 --> 01:42:53.368
Swim to shore as fast as you can!

913
01:42:53.458 --> 01:42:54.538
Hold on. Preston!

914
01:42:55.208 --> 01:42:57.580
Whatever happens. don't
let go of the camera!

915
01:42:57.670 --> 01:42:59.250
Don't let go of the camera!

916
01:43:07.053 --> 01:43:08.843
Come on. get
up out of that water.

917
01:43:10.344 --> 01:43:11.644
Get up!

918
01:43:51.436 --> 01:43:52.936
Come on. come on.

919
01:44:05.280 --> 01:44:07.240
Preston. Preston.

920
01:44:18.923 --> 01:44:20.133
It's working.

921
01:44:38.488 --> 01:44:40.489
Did you get that. did you?

922
01:45:40.845 --> 01:45:42.176
No!

923
01:45:43.017 --> 01:45:44.187
No.

924
01:45:48.478 --> 01:45:49.559
No.

925
01:46:39.992 --> 01:46:41.333
What is it?

926
01:46:45.874 --> 01:46:47.205
Mr Hayes?

927
01:46:50.757 --> 01:46:53.337
If anything happens.
I want you to run.

928
01:46:53.847 --> 01:46:55.347
You understand?

929
01:46:55.637 --> 01:46:58.848
I'm not a coward. I ain't gonna run.

930
01:47:00.178 --> 01:47:02.640
It's not about being brave. Jimmy.

931
01:47:30.887 --> 01:47:32.048
Go back!

932
01:47:33.758 --> 01:47:35.429
Back across the log!

933
01:47:35.509 --> 01:47:38.219
- I ain't gonna run!
- Get Jimmy out of here!

934
01:47:38.309 --> 01:47:39.979
- No!
- Get back! Get back!

935
01:47:44.400 --> 01:47:45.731
Move back!

936
01:47:58.705 --> 01:48:01.085
- No! No!
- Stay back.

937
01:48:03.585 --> 01:48:04.665
No!

938
01:48:10.009 --> 01:48:11.429
Look at me.

939
01:48:13.599 --> 01:48:16.179
Let him go!
- You got to run. Jimmy.

940
01:48:20.391 --> 01:48:21.891
Do as I say.

941
01:48:22.943 --> 01:48:24.443
Go with Jack.

942
01:48:26.943 --> 01:48:28.363
Run!

943
01:48:31.534 --> 01:48:33.955
- No!
- Shoot him!

944
01:48:51.429 --> 01:48:54.221
Here! Over here!

945
01:49:12.455 --> 01:49:14.417
Hold on! Hold on!

946
01:49:18.497 --> 01:49:21.127
Lumpy! Help me!

947
01:49:23.007 --> 01:49:24.418
Bloody hell. Choy!

948
01:54:46.109 --> 01:54:47.189
No!

949
01:54:51.361 --> 01:54:52.572
Oh. my!

950
02:01:28.044 --> 02:01:29.384
Wait!

951
02:02:18.848 --> 02:02:20.098
Carl.

952
02:02:25.069 --> 02:02:26.779
Jimmy. Jimmy.

953
02:02:29.490 --> 02:02:30.951
You all right?

954
02:03:20.754 --> 02:03:22.166
No.

955
02:04:14.270 --> 02:04:16.311
Get off! Get it off!

956
02:04:23.862 --> 02:04:24.992
Get off!

957
02:04:38.837 --> 02:04:40.217
Get it off!

958
02:04:40.797 --> 02:04:42.337
Get it off! Get it off!

959
02:05:45.786 --> 02:05:47.076
Kill it!

960
02:05:59.009 --> 02:06:00.429
Stop moving!

961
02:06:20.486 --> 02:06:22.196
Get it off my face!

962
02:06:23.156 --> 02:06:25.576
- Stay still.
- I am standing still.

963
02:06:28.077 --> 02:06:29.878
- Hold on.
- Be careful!

964
02:07:04.708 --> 02:07:07.369
Don't move!
Stay away from the walls!

965
02:07:08.039 --> 02:07:09.539
Coming through!

966
02:07:18.011 --> 02:07:20.592
Get out of there now! Climb!

967
02:07:28.064 --> 02:07:29.894
Nobody get in my way.

968
02:07:32.854 --> 02:07:34.616
Come on. Jimmy. Let's go.

969
02:07:34.696 --> 02:07:37.578
Get up the rope. Let's go. Hurry up.

970
02:08:03.894 --> 02:08:05.974
Jimmy. let's go.

971
02:08:10.606 --> 02:08:12.197
- Come on.
- Okay.

972
02:08:15.408 --> 02:08:16.529
Go.

973
02:08:21.370 --> 02:08:23.250
Just as you go down...

974
02:08:24.290 --> 02:08:26.580
for the third and final time...

975
02:08:27.632 --> 02:08:30.553
as your head disappears
beneath the waves...

976
02:08:31.133 --> 02:08:33.553
and your lungs fill with water...

977
02:08:33.803 --> 02:08:38.093
do you know what happens in those
last precious seconds before you drown?

978
02:08:38.343 --> 02:08:41.224
Come on. buddy. Get up the rope.
Come on. Get out of here. Come on.

979
02:08:41.305 --> 02:08:43.976
Your whole life passes
before your eyes.

980
02:08:44.066 --> 02:08:46.527
And if you've lived
as a true American...

981
02:08:46.607 --> 02:08:48.647
you get to watch it all in colour.

982
02:08:49.857 --> 02:08:51.487
Oh. and you will.

983
02:08:51.567 --> 02:08:54.239
Now. why don't you climb
up the rope. huh? Come on.

984
02:08:59.450 --> 02:09:01.541
Come on. Driscoll. Let's go.

985
02:11:56.231 --> 02:11:57.771
It's beautiful.

986
02:12:19.216 --> 02:12:20.546
Beautiful.

987
02:12:32.061 --> 02:12:33.401
Beautiful.

988
02:13:20.784 --> 02:13:21.994
There.

989
02:13:25.075 --> 02:13:28.165
Thank God.
- Don't thank God. Thank Mr Baxter.

990
02:13:28.285 --> 02:13:30.626
He insisted on a rescue mission.

991
02:13:31.626 --> 02:13:35.088
Me? I knew you'd be okay.

992
02:13:36.379 --> 02:13:38.629
That's the thing about cockroaches.

993
02:13:38.719 --> 02:13:42.140
No matter how many times you
flush them down the toilet...

994
02:13:42.220 --> 02:13:44.720
they always crawl back up the bowl.

995
02:13:45.640 --> 02:13:48.481
Hey. buddy? I'm out of the bowl.

996
02:13:49.272 --> 02:13:52.523
I'm drying off my wings
and trekking across the lid.

997
02:13:59.864 --> 02:14:01.115
Driscoll!

998
02:14:02.575 --> 02:14:06.247
Don't be a fool! Give
it up. It's useless!

999
02:14:07.498 --> 02:14:08.878
She's dead.

1000
02:14:11.668 --> 02:14:13.258
She's not dead.

1001
02:14:17.180 --> 02:14:19.390
Jack's gonna bring her back...

1002
02:14:20.350 --> 02:14:22.970
and the ape will be
hard on his heels.

1003
02:14:23.741 --> 02:14:26.450
We can still come out
of this thing okay.

1004
02:14:28.868 --> 02:14:30.408
More than okay.

1005
02:14:31.657 --> 02:14:33.246
Think about it.

1006
02:14:33.326 --> 02:14:36.993
You got a boat full of chloroform
we could put to good use.

1007
02:14:37.083 --> 02:14:38.952
You wanna trap the ape?

1008
02:14:45.788 --> 02:14:47.416
I don't think so.

1009
02:14:47.996 --> 02:14:51.413
Isn't that what you
do? Live animal capture?

1010
02:14:52.913 --> 02:14:54.951
I heard you were the best.

1011
02:15:02.786 --> 02:15:03.915
Jack!

1012
02:15:07.003 --> 02:15:08.751
Look after yourself!

1013
02:15:09.411 --> 02:15:11.330
Keep the gate open. will you?

1014
02:15:11.420 --> 02:15:13.080
Sure thing. buddy.

1015
02:15:13.839 --> 02:15:15.169
Good luck!

1016
02:15:28.419 --> 02:15:29.798
I'm sorry.

1017
02:18:08.523 --> 02:18:09.613
Ann.

1018
02:19:18.077 --> 02:19:19.166
Jack!

1019
02:19:20.036 --> 02:19:21.166
Run!

1020
02:19:51.415 --> 02:19:53.044
Jack. Jack!

1021
02:20:00.748 --> 02:20:01.917
Jack.

1022
02:20:10.962 --> 02:20:12.922
Ann. it's okay.

1023
02:20:13.841 --> 02:20:16.209
Ann. let's go. Let's go. Come on!

1024
02:20:29.420 --> 02:20:31.049
Let's go. Come on.

1025
02:20:31.509 --> 02:20:32.758
Come on!

1026
02:22:04.937 --> 02:22:06.017
Carl!

1027
02:22:06.186 --> 02:22:09.105
Please! Somebody help us!

1028
02:22:11.023 --> 02:22:12.522
They've gone.

1029
02:22:14.061 --> 02:22:16.150
Carl. Christ.

1030
02:22:16.690 --> 02:22:17.809
Carl!

1031
02:22:18.648 --> 02:22:20.817
Drop the bridge. Do it
now. for Christ's sake!

1032
02:22:20.897 --> 02:22:22.106
Not yet.

1033
02:22:23.525 --> 02:22:24.645
Wait.

1034
02:22:25.314 --> 02:22:26.403
Wait.

1035
02:22:30.520 --> 02:22:31.649
Wait!

1036
02:22:42.362 --> 02:22:43.572
Come on!

1037
02:23:55.993 --> 02:23:57.492
- Now!
- Throw them!

1038
02:23:57.582 --> 02:23:58.952
Throw!

1039
02:23:59.831 --> 02:24:00.871
No!

1040
02:24:03.209 --> 02:24:04.458
Hold him!

1041
02:24:04.538 --> 02:24:06.536
Are you out of your mind?

1042
02:24:14.701 --> 02:24:16.870
- Stop!
- Hold the line!

1043
02:24:17.581 --> 02:24:19.000
Keep him down!

1044
02:24:24.705 --> 02:24:26.204
Heave!

1045
02:24:26.584 --> 02:24:27.913
Please!

1046
02:24:28.373 --> 02:24:30.081
No! Stop!

1047
02:24:30.421 --> 02:24:31.500
Jack.

1048
02:24:33.129 --> 02:24:34.458
- No.
- Get her out of...

1049
02:24:34.538 --> 02:24:36.208
- They'll kill him!
- There's nothing we can do.

1050
02:24:36.298 --> 02:24:37.747
- No!
- Get her out of his sight!

1051
02:24:37.837 --> 02:24:39.755
It's too late.
- Throw it!

1052
02:24:42.043 --> 02:24:43.122
Look out!

1053
02:24:45.421 --> 02:24:46.920
Let go of me.

1054
02:24:51.046 --> 02:24:52.666
We gotta go. Come on.

1055
02:24:53.255 --> 02:24:54.416
- Come on.
- Stop it.

1056
02:24:54.506 --> 02:24:56.045
Leave me alone!

1057
02:24:57.214 --> 02:24:58.753
Ann. please come on.

1058
02:25:06.048 --> 02:25:07.876
- Kill it!
No. No!

1059
02:25:08.086 --> 02:25:10.335
It's over. you goddamn lunatic!

1060
02:25:12.543 --> 02:25:14.093
All of you. run!

1061
02:25:14.173 --> 02:25:15.801
Come on. Come on!

1062
02:25:32.760 --> 02:25:34.339
Look out!

1063
02:25:45.092 --> 02:25:46.761
Move it! Move it!

1064
02:25:49.099 --> 02:25:50.468
Come on. come on!

1065
02:25:59.392 --> 02:26:01.012
- Stay there!
- It's me he wants!

1066
02:26:01.102 --> 02:26:03.260
- Please stop this!
- Move! Hold onto her!

1067
02:26:03.350 --> 02:26:06.018
- Ann. go.
- Please. I can stop this!

1068
02:26:06.098 --> 02:26:07.596
- No!
- Ann. stay there!

1069
02:26:10.095 --> 02:26:11.474
Get it out!

1070
02:26:14.222 --> 02:26:16.101
Get the hell out of here!

1071
02:26:16.181 --> 02:26:18.140
- Come on!
- Jimmy. don't be crazy! Come on.

1072
02:26:18.220 --> 02:26:19.520
Don't be crazy.

1073
02:26:20.729 --> 02:26:21.808
Let me go!

1074
02:26:23.147 --> 02:26:24.596
Cast off!

1075
02:26:26.934 --> 02:26:28.183
Come on. Carl!

1076
02:26:29.643 --> 02:26:31.481
- Row!
Wait.

1077
02:26:31.771 --> 02:26:33.890
Row. God damn it!

1078
02:26:44.802 --> 02:26:45.971
Go back.

1079
02:26:52.887 --> 02:26:53.966
Jimmy. no!

1080
02:27:00.972 --> 02:27:02.011
No!

1081
02:27:19.139 --> 02:27:21.438
No! Don't! Leave him alone!

1082
02:27:21.517 --> 02:27:23.016
Hide out in back!

1083
02:27:44.984 --> 02:27:46.642
- Wait!
- No!

1084
02:27:47.312 --> 02:27:49.939
No! No! Please don't!

1085
02:29:48.042 --> 02:29:50.580
The whole world
will pay to see this.

1086
02:29:53.327 --> 02:29:55.326
We're millionaires. boys!

1087
02:29:55.626 --> 02:29:57.836
I'll share it with all of you!

1088
02:29:58.335 --> 02:30:02.831
In a few months. his name will
be up in lights on Broadway!

1089
02:30:05.000 --> 02:30:09.127
Kong! The Eighth
Wonder of the World!

1090
02:31:09.865 --> 02:31:11.155
Mr Denham!

1091
02:31:12.245 --> 02:31:14.286
What can I say? What can I say?

1092
02:31:14.366 --> 02:31:15.747
Any comments. Mr Denham?

1093
02:31:17.077 --> 02:31:18.747
The Mayor. thank you.

1094
02:31:19.917 --> 02:31:20.997
Ready.

1095
02:31:21.087 --> 02:31:22.418
What am I?

1096
02:31:22.838 --> 02:31:24.588
Thank you very much.

1097
02:31:28.429 --> 02:31:29.930
Get used to it.

1098
02:31:30.140 --> 02:31:33.310
- Listen. it's great to see you. Ready?
- I'm really appreciating that...

1099
02:31:33.390 --> 02:31:34.850
- Look at you!
- I remember you.

1100
02:31:34.930 --> 02:31:37.931
- You're a lucky guy. Denham.
- Am I a lucky guy?

1101
02:31:38.021 --> 02:31:39.812
Maybe you're the lucky guy.

1102
02:31:53.615 --> 02:31:54.785
Carl!

1103
02:31:56.665 --> 02:31:57.835
- Zelman!
- I told them.

1104
02:31:57.915 --> 02:31:59.335
I know you did and I appreciate it.

1105
02:31:59.415 --> 02:32:01.376
Let's get a shot of this.

1106
02:32:01.916 --> 02:32:03.047
Come on.

1107
02:32:03.797 --> 02:32:06.427
- Big smile.
- Yeah! That's great!

1108
02:32:08.508 --> 02:32:11.428
Look at yourself.
Look at what you've become.

1109
02:32:12.178 --> 02:32:14.679
- No woman is worth this.
This woman is worth it.

1110
02:32:14.769 --> 02:32:16.770
I don't care what it
takes. I gotta win her back.

1111
02:32:16.850 --> 02:32:18.060
Oh. really?

1112
02:32:18.140 --> 02:32:19.810
She's not gonna buy
this for a second.

1113
02:32:19.900 --> 02:32:22.060
Shut up and hand me the grapefruit!

1114
02:32:24.191 --> 02:32:26.862
- You're writing a comedy?
- Yes. I am.

1115
02:32:27.612 --> 02:32:29.532
I'm writing it for you.

1116
02:32:31.492 --> 02:32:33.363
Why would you do that?

1117
02:32:34.373 --> 02:32:36.743
Why would I
write a play for you?

1118
02:32:40.165 --> 02:32:41.795
Isn't it obvious?

1119
02:32:42.045 --> 02:32:43.545
Oh. I'm sorry.

1120
02:32:44.795 --> 02:32:47.005
I couldn't help but overhear.

1121
02:32:50.177 --> 02:32:52.887
So. he took me to this
fancy French restaurant...

1122
02:32:52.967 --> 02:32:55.768
and halfway through the hors
d'oeuvres. he clutches my hand.

1123
02:32:55.848 --> 02:32:58.058
And that's when he
told you how he felt?

1124
02:32:58.138 --> 02:33:00.849
- No. He never said it.
- He never said it?

1125
02:33:00.939 --> 02:33:02.900
He probably thought he
didn't need to say it.

1126
02:33:02.980 --> 02:33:04.980
Well. then how does
she know that it's real?

1127
02:33:05.070 --> 02:33:08.530
- He said it was not about the words.
- Oh. please!

1128
02:33:08.740 --> 02:33:12.862
If you feel it. you say
it. It's really very simple.

1129
02:33:13.242 --> 02:33:17.532
He said we'd talk about it
later. Only there was no later.

1130
02:33:19.243 --> 02:33:20.913
It never happened.

1131
02:33:21.833 --> 02:33:23.583
That's how it ended.

1132
02:33:23.753 --> 02:33:27.465
He just let you walk away?
He didn't try to save it?

1133
02:33:29.345 --> 02:33:32.715
I honestly believed things
might actually work out...

1134
02:33:33.805 --> 02:33:35.807
which was really very...

1135
02:33:39.097 --> 02:33:40.307
foolish.

1136
02:33:40.557 --> 02:33:43.188
Men. Oh. they'll
give you the world...

1137
02:33:43.268 --> 02:33:45.648
but they let the one
thing that truly matters...

1138
02:33:45.728 --> 02:33:47.609
slip through their fingers.

1139
02:33:47.689 --> 02:33:48.949
Typical.

1140
02:33:49.530 --> 02:33:53.200
They're so busy being brave.
they forget to use their brains.

1141
02:33:54.160 --> 02:33:56.080
Romance. Who needs it?

1142
02:34:20.806 --> 02:34:22.146
Thank you.

1143
02:34:22.977 --> 02:34:24.357
Thank you.

1144
02:34:27.277 --> 02:34:28.608
Thank you.

1145
02:34:30.448 --> 02:34:31.778
Thank you.

1146
02:34:33.618 --> 02:34:35.489
Ladies and gentlemen...

1147
02:34:36.660 --> 02:34:39.500
I'm here to tell you
a very strange story.

1148
02:34:39.950 --> 02:34:42.170
The story of our adventure...

1149
02:34:42.500 --> 02:34:45.711
in which 17 of our party
suffered horrible deaths...

1150
02:34:46.462 --> 02:34:48.172
their lives lost...

1151
02:34:48.712 --> 02:34:51.012
in pursuit of a savage beast...

1152
02:34:51.963 --> 02:34:54.593
a monstrous aberration of nature.

1153
02:34:55.803 --> 02:34:58.514
But even the meanest
brute can be tamed.

1154
02:34:58.684 --> 02:35:01.395
Yes. ladies and gentlemen.
as you will see...

1155
02:35:01.475 --> 02:35:03.475
the beast was no match...

1156
02:35:03.725 --> 02:35:05.735
for the charms of a girl.

1157
02:35:08.776 --> 02:35:10.657
A girl from New York...

1158
02:35:13.577 --> 02:35:15.368
who melted his heart...

1159
02:35:16.078 --> 02:35:18.948
bringing to mind that
old Arabian proverb...

1160
02:35:20.618 --> 02:35:24.000
"And lo. the beast looked
upon the face of beauty...

1161
02:35:24.830 --> 02:35:26.960
"and beauty stayed his hand.

1162
02:35:28.000 --> 02:35:31.881
"And from that day forward.
he was as one dead."

1163
02:35:39.683 --> 02:35:43.143
And now. ladies and gentlemen.
I'm going to show you...

1164
02:35:43.273 --> 02:35:46.275
the greatest thing your
eyes have ever beheld.

1165
02:35:47.395 --> 02:35:52.065
He was a king in the world he knew.
but he comes to you now a captive.

1166
02:35:53.275 --> 02:35:54.946
Ladies and gentlemen...

1167
02:35:55.036 --> 02:35:59.577
I give you Kong. The
Eighth Wonder of the World!

1168
02:36:08.919 --> 02:36:12.050
Don't be alarmed.
It's perfectly safe.

1169
02:36:12.380 --> 02:36:15.800
These chains are
made of chrome steel!

1170
02:36:36.575 --> 02:36:38.365
Observe. if you will...

1171
02:36:41.626 --> 02:36:43.577
I am touching the beast.

1172
02:36:43.917 --> 02:36:48.127
I am actually laying my
hand on the 25-foot gorilla.

1173
02:36:55.259 --> 02:36:56.930
Crank them up. fellas.

1174
02:37:16.243 --> 02:37:18.454
And now. we have in the
auditorium tonight...

1175
02:37:18.534 --> 02:37:20.115
a surprise guest.

1176
02:37:20.955 --> 02:37:23.335
The real-life hero of this story.

1177
02:37:23.535 --> 02:37:26.245
The man who hunted
down the mighty Kong!

1178
02:37:27.626 --> 02:37:32.427
The man who risked all to win
the freedom of a helpless female.

1179
02:37:33.587 --> 02:37:35.928
A big hand for Mr Bruce Baxter!

1180
02:37:41.809 --> 02:37:43.640
Thank you. Thank you.

1181
02:37:44.640 --> 02:37:45.980
Thank you.

1182
02:38:13.385 --> 02:38:14.846
He was right.

1183
02:38:16.387 --> 02:38:19.927
About there still being some
mystery left in this world...

1184
02:38:20.347 --> 02:38:22.888
and we can all have a piece of it...

1185
02:38:23.018 --> 02:38:25.598
for the price of
an admission ticket.

1186
02:38:26.858 --> 02:38:29.900
That's the thing you
come to learn about Carl.

1187
02:38:31.280 --> 02:38:34.690
His unfailing ability to
destroy the things he loves.

1188
02:38:49.123 --> 02:38:51.714
Please remain calm.
ladies and gentlemen...

1189
02:38:51.794 --> 02:38:55.095
for we now come to the
climax of this savage ritual.

1190
02:38:55.295 --> 02:38:58.015
The sacrifice of a
beautiful young girl.

1191
02:38:58.555 --> 02:39:02.226
Behold her terror as she is
offered up to the mighty Kong!

1192
02:39:03.437 --> 02:39:07.517
A big hand. folks. for the
bravest girl I've ever met!

1193
02:39:08.227 --> 02:39:09.858
Miss Ann Darrow.

1194
02:39:57.488 --> 02:39:59.238
Save me from the beast!

1195
02:40:08.120 --> 02:40:09.330
Help me!

1196
02:40:13.462 --> 02:40:14.962
Where is she?

1197
02:40:15.962 --> 02:40:17.512
- Where's Ann?
- I have no idea.

1198
02:40:17.592 --> 02:40:20.973
I heard he offered her all kinds of
money and she turned him down flat.

1199
02:40:21.053 --> 02:40:25.764
Pack up all my cares and woe

1200
02:40:27.515 --> 02:40:28.975
Here I go

1201
02:40:30.315 --> 02:40:31.985
Singing low

1202
02:40:34.236 --> 02:40:36.277
Bye bye

1203
02:40:38.657 --> 02:40:40.077
Blackbird

1204
02:40:45.328 --> 02:40:49.669
Where somebody waits for me

1205
02:40:51.130 --> 02:40:52.710
Sugar's sweet

1206
02:40:54.170 --> 02:40:55.920
So is he

1207
02:40:58.261 --> 02:40:59.972
Bye bye

1208
02:41:02.092 --> 02:41:04.682
Blackbird

1209
02:41:06.813 --> 02:41:08.143
Here's your story. boys.

1210
02:41:08.223 --> 02:41:11.314
"Beauty and the man who
saved her from the beast."

1211
02:41:26.367 --> 02:41:28.247
We have to get these
people out of here.

1212
02:41:28.327 --> 02:41:30.838
Everyone needs to
leave. okay? Come on.

1213
02:41:32.038 --> 02:41:34.629
Let him roar. It
makes a swell picture.

1214
02:41:36.089 --> 02:41:37.130
Head for the exits.

1215
02:41:37.220 --> 02:41:40.010
Get your own seat. buddy.
You're not having mine.

1216
02:41:47.812 --> 02:41:49.272
Excuse me. fellows.

1217
02:41:49.982 --> 02:41:52.693
Coming through. Coming
through. fellows.

1218
02:41:56.233 --> 02:41:59.234
Get me down! Help me. please!

1219
02:42:01.655 --> 02:42:04.575
Somebody! Somebody help me!

1220
02:42:07.956 --> 02:42:10.627
Go! Go! Get out!

1221
02:42:14.587 --> 02:42:16.088
Go! Go!

1222
02:43:51.098 --> 02:43:53.558
There they are. Come
on. come with me.

1223
02:44:06.322 --> 02:44:07.992
- Go!
- Wait for me!

1224
02:44:08.912 --> 02:44:10.292
Go back!

1225
02:44:17.293 --> 02:44:18.544
This way!

1226
02:44:26.345 --> 02:44:27.515
Help!

1227
02:44:35.898 --> 02:44:37.068
No!

1228
02:45:16.817 --> 02:45:19.487
Taxi! Follow that ape.

1229
02:45:19.567 --> 02:45:21.067
Come on. pal. we gotta draw him off.

1230
02:45:21.157 --> 02:45:22.948
It's all yours. buddy.

1231
02:45:39.381 --> 02:45:41.052
Better
get out of here. lady!

1232
02:46:01.816 --> 02:46:03.067
Come on.

1233
02:46:12.248 --> 02:46:13.368
Buddy!

1234
02:46:14.578 --> 02:46:16.790
Come on. Come on.

1235
02:46:35.603 --> 02:46:36.853
Look out.

1236
02:46:59.668 --> 02:47:00.918
Jesus Christ.

1237
02:52:24.208 --> 02:52:25.128
Fire!

1238
02:52:27.548 --> 02:52:28.629
Stop!

1239
02:52:44.192 --> 02:52:45.652
Listen up.

1240
02:52:45.733 --> 02:52:48.693
This is New York City.
and this is sacred ground.

1241
02:52:48.773 --> 02:52:50.233
You hear me?

1242
02:52:50.863 --> 02:52:53.495
It was built for humans. by humans.

1243
02:52:53.575 --> 02:52:55.905
Not for stinking
lice-infested apes.

1244
02:52:56.155 --> 02:52:57.915
The thought of some
mutant gorilla...

1245
02:52:57.995 --> 02:53:02.706
crapping all over the streets of
this fair city. fills me with disgust.

1246
02:53:02.796 --> 02:53:04.797
So this is how it's gonna be.

1247
02:53:04.877 --> 02:53:07.217
We find it. We kill it.

1248
02:53:07.297 --> 02:53:10.548
We cut its ugly head
off and we ram it up...

1249
02:53:30.572 --> 02:53:32.443
No. No.

1250
02:56:03.685 --> 02:56:05.015
Beautiful.

1251
02:56:11.447 --> 02:56:12.527
Yes.

1252
02:56:15.157 --> 02:56:16.528
Yes. it is.

1253
03:01:10.040 --> 03:01:11.290
Look at that.

1254
03:01:13.131 --> 03:01:14.252
Hey! Hey!

1255
03:01:14.502 --> 03:01:16.462
Nobody past this point.

1256
03:01:17.382 --> 03:01:19.302
You can't go in there!

1257
03:01:23.473 --> 03:01:24.763
Stop him!

1258
03:01:27.855 --> 03:01:30.145
Hey! Get back. You're
not allowed up there!

1259
03:01:30.225 --> 03:01:31.855
- What's going on?
- Go!

1260
03:05:13.743 --> 03:05:15.043
No!

1261
03:05:16.213 --> 03:05:19.254
No!

1262
03:05:25.345 --> 03:05:27.965
Please! No!

1263
03:05:28.345 --> 03:05:29.476
No!

1264
03:08:26.154 --> 03:08:28.445
Ann. Ann.

1265
03:09:17.785 --> 03:09:19.085
Move along.

1266
03:09:19.545 --> 03:09:21.455
Just
one shot! One shot!

1267
03:09:22.126 --> 03:09:24.217
- Come. come!
- Boys. how about a photo?

1268
03:09:24.297 --> 03:09:25.337
Look at me.

1269
03:09:25.417 --> 03:09:27.177
Come on. watch the camera.

1270
03:09:29.968 --> 03:09:31.508
Come a little closer.

1271
03:09:32.178 --> 03:09:34.348
That's it. folks.
Show's over. Step back!

1272
03:09:34.428 --> 03:09:36.639
Clear the area. That's
it. Shove off. boys.

1273
03:09:37.349 --> 03:09:38.890
Why'd he do that?

1274
03:09:39.190 --> 03:09:41.690
Climb up there and
get himself cornered.

1275
03:09:41.770 --> 03:09:44.070
The ape must have
known what was coming.

1276
03:09:44.150 --> 03:09:46.821
He's just a dumb animal.
Didn't know nothing.

1277
03:09:53.033 --> 03:09:55.743
What does it matter?
Airplanes got him.

1278
03:09:58.333 --> 03:10:00.294
It wasn't the airplanes.

1279
03:10:04.675 --> 03:10:06.965
It was beauty killed the beast.

1280
03:10:07.305 --> 03:11:07.503
